  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677854237877-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677854237877-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677854237877-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677854237877-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1677854237877-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677854261348-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677854261348-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677854261348-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677854261348-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1677854261348-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pod[s]</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Discard the <strong>outer green pod[s]</strong> and add the <strong>cardamom seed[s]</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar </strong>with your <strong>black mustard seeds </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and roughly bash until you end up with a coarse powder – this is your <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>chopped green beans </strong>with your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>spice mix </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677854271407-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677854271407-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677854271407-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677854271407-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1677854271407-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>tamari soy sauce</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677854281467-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677854281467-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677854281467-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677854281467-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1677854281467-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium high and add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong></p><p>Remove your <strong>pineapple</strong> from the can (save the juice!) and chop roughly into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> reserved pineapple juice</strong> to the pan</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677854294534-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677854294534-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677854294534-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677854294534-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1677854294534-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped pineapple </strong>and cook, covered, for 3-4 min or until thickened to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>Sri Lankan-style pineapple & chickpea curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677854304558-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677854304558-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677854304558-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677854304558-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1677854304558-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the curry is cooking, squeeze your pouch[es] of<strong> cooked white long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1677854313164-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1677854313164-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1677854313164-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1677854313164-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1677854313164-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Sri Lankan-style pineapple & chickpea curry </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
